Condition : 3 - No development above ground level shall take place until full details and samples of all materials to be used in the construction of the external surfaces of the development hereby permitted have been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. Details must include a detailed schedule of materials, a photographic sample board, elevations and sections at a sufficient scale to illustrate how all external materials will appear together.
The [samples/details] shall include:
(a) Cladding materials / render (including specifications where relevant);
(b) Tiles / roof covering; including parapet coping / capping materials, dormers and canopies;
(c) Window and door types; (including details / sections / materials)
(d) All privacy measures (including obscure glazing details, privacy screens etc.);
(e) Canopy details, balustrading treatment to external and roof areas if any (including details / sections / materials); and handrails
(f) Balustrading treatment (including details / sections / materials); and
(g) Any other materials / details / fittings to be used (including solar panels, extract vents, boiler flues, hard landscaping, etc.), with sections and on-site samples where appropriate
The development shall then be carried out in accordance with the approved details and maintained as such thereafter.

Condition : 14 - No development shall take place until a Construction Logistics Plan (CLP), written in accordance with current TfL guidance, has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The CLP shall include:
(a) a site plan (showing the elements set out below);
(b) confirmation that a pre-start record of site conditions on the adjoining public highway will be undertaken with Hounslow Highways and a commitment to repair any damage caused;
(c) provision for the parking of vehicles of site operatives and visitors;
(d) provisions for loading, unloading and storage of plant and materials within the site;
(e) details of access to the site, including means to control and manage access and egress of vehicles to and from the site for the duration of construction including phasing arrangements;
(f) details of vehicle routeing from the site to the wider strategic road network;
(g) the erection and maintenance of security hoarding including decorative displays and facilities for public viewing, where appropriate;
(h) provision of wheel washing facilities at the site exit and a commitment to sweep adjacent roads when required and at the request of the Council;
(i) a scheme for recycling/disposing of waste resulting from demolition and construction works;
(j) measures to ensure the safety of all users of the public highway especially cyclists and pedestrians in the vicinity of the site and especially at the access;
(k) commitment to liaise with other contractors in the vicinity of the site to maximise the potential for consolidation and to minimise traffic impacts;
(l) avoidance of peak hours for deliveries and details of a booking system to avoid vehicles waiting on the public highway;
(m) all necessary traffic orders and other permissions required to allow safe access to the site to be secured and implemented prior to commencement of construction;
(n) details of the construction programme and a schedule of traffic movements;
(o) the use of opera

Condition : 15 - Notwithstanding the submitted details, before the development hereby permitted is first occupied or brought into use, an updated Parking Management Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The Plan shall include the following:
(i) A commitment to review and fully justify the number of parking spaces once the end-user is known, and details of how this will be operated and enforced;
(ii) details of measures proposed to restrict parking to designated bays only and prohibit parking on the access road;
(iii) a commitment to convert passive EV bays to active and to provide additional Blue Badge bays when demand requires;
(iv) details of the operation of any gates or barriers;
(v) details of how parking will be monitored and managed during shift changeovers;
(vi) measures to ensure that all prospective occupiers are informed of the Parking Management Plan.
The parking areas and access road(s) shall thereafter be managed in compliance with the approved Parking Management Plan, unless the prior written approval of the local planning authority is obtained to secure any variation.
